<paragraph id="3D7697363576FFE1FEF7F9D46503F9BA" blockId="26.[264,1325,284,1798]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Etymology. Latin 
<taxonomicName id="FAC9ECB53576FFE1FDDEF9D4655DF9E1" authorityName="Scarbrough Table Of Contents" authorityYear="2005" box="[529,628,1572,1597]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Afroestricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamulus">
<emphasis id="0FBD4B243576FFE1FDDEF9D4655DF9E1" box="[529,628,1572,1597]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">hamulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for small hook, referring to the shape of the ventroapical corner of the epandrium.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D7697363576FFE1FEF7F9846205F952" blockId="26.[264,1325,284,1798]" box="[312,1324,1652,1678]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
